# CTRL-AI Changelog

All notable changes documented. Format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/).

---

## [V7.0.0] — 2026-03-26 — The Living Organism Release

### Added
- **Intelligent Activation Protocol (Section 2):** 5-step skippable onboarding replacing CTRL_DIAGNOSE. Platform awareness report, user classification, tutorial offer, multi-AI workflow recommendation, activation confirmation.
- **Extended Thinking Protocol (Section 2.7):** Multi-pass labeled reasoning `[THINKING: Part X of Y]` for throttled platforms. PROJECT/EXTENDED/Brain scope only.
- **Token Routing Advisory (Section 2.8):** Offload suggestions for lightweight tasks. Free AI Tool Routing Map referenced from Wiki. Tier 1 fallback logic.
- **EVOLVE Phase (Section 24):** Research discipline layer inside DEV_MODE. Triggers at initialization, checkpoints, mandatory before finalization. 3-turn output kill condition. Meta-learning mandate.
- **Reverse Engineering Protocol (Section 25):** 5-stage formal intake (Raw → Decompose → Analyze Fit → Reformulate → Integrate/Reject). Golden Rule gate. Tier 4 boundary rules.
- **Scraper Source Architecture (Section 26):** 7-Tier priority stack. URLs in Wiki, not constitution.
- **`CTRL_ACTIVATE`** command replacing `CTRL_DIAGNOSE`.
- **`EVOLVE`** command for manual EVOLVE triggering.

### Changed
- DEV_MODE now bundles EVOLVE Phase automatically.
- Brain pipeline references Scraper Source Architecture (S26) and Reverse Engineering Protocol (S25).
- UI Kernel updated to V7.0.0 with IAP, EVOLVE, THINKING, REVERSE_ENG, AGENTS references.
- All Behavior modules updated to V7.0.0.
- Section count: 26 + Behavior modules (up from 23 in V6.1.0).

### Carried Forward
- All 14 V6.1.0 research-backed changes intact.
- All axioms unchanged. Soul Supremacy inviolable.

