## [V6.1.0] — 2026-03-26 — Research Integration & Runtime Hardening

### Added
- Version Authority & Canonical Control (header + version check).
- Model-family Q4 in Tier Detector for reasoning-native models.
- Lexical Translation Matrix (Section 10A.1): 10-verb expansion table.
- Dispute Resolution guidance (Section 4.4) with INVESTIGATE FURTHER option.
- SCEL Pre-Final Compliance Stamp: `[COMPLIANCE: PTRR ✓ | Evidence ✓ | Task Sep ✓]`.
- SCEL Enforcement Limitation disclosure.
- Spike deliberation-depth secondary trigger.
- SYS_MEM Beliefs convention (`~` prefix).
- No-solicitation clause (Section 21).
- Evidence Tagging guidance (Section 8.3A).
- Platform adapters: Perplexity, Kimi.
- Agent Spawning governed state mandate.
- CTRL_MIGRATE governed state format (raw only under DEBUG).
- Sycophancy trigger visibility in SYS_MEM.
- QUICK mode SCEL exemption rationale.

### Validated by Cross-AI Analysis
- 87 items analyzed across 6 models (Opus, GPT, Codex, Sonnet, Composer, Claude).
- 7 items rejected to Rejection Ledger with revival conditions.
- Soul/axioms confirmed unanimous across all models.

